Menu="Utilities"
Title="ShipLog"
Icon="anchor"
---
<?php
/* ShipLog plugin settings. Writes /boot/config/plugins/shiplog/shiplog.cfg via
   Unraid's /update.php, then restarts the engine daemon. */
$cfg = parse_plugin_cfg("shiplog", true);
function v($cfg, $k, $def = "") { return htmlspecialchars(isset($cfg[$k]) && $cfg[$k] !== "" ? $cfg[$k] : $def); }
?>

<form markdown="1" name="shiplog_settings" method="POST" action="/update.php" target="progressFrame">
<input type="hidden" name="#file" value="shiplog/shiplog.cfg">
<input type="hidden" name="#command" value="/usr/local/emhttp/plugins/shiplog/scripts/rc.shiplog">
<input type="hidden" name="#arg[1]" value="restart">

_(Enable engine)_:
: <select name="ENABLE">
  <option value="true"  <?=v($cfg,'ENABLE','true')!=='false'?'selected':''?>>Yes</option>
  <option value="false" <?=v($cfg,'ENABLE','true')==='false'?'selected':''?>>No</option>
  </select>

_(Engine port)_:
: <input type="text" class="narrow" name="PORT" value="<?=v($cfg,'PORT','8484')?>"> &nbsp; <span id="sl-statuslink"></span>

_(Data directory)_:
: <input type="text" name="DATA_DIR" value="<?=v($cfg,'DATA_DIR','/mnt/user/appdata/shiplog')?>"> (SQLite cache — keep on appdata, not the flash)

_(Poll interval)_:
: <input type="text" class="narrow" name="POLL_INTERVAL" value="<?=v($cfg,'POLL_INTERVAL','6h')?>"> (Go duration, e.g. 1h, 6h, 24h)

_(GitHub token)_:
: <input type="password" name="GITHUB_TOKEN" value="<?=v($cfg,'GITHUB_TOKEN')?>"> (optional — raises the changelog API rate limit)

> **Optional — AI summaries (Ollama)**

_(Ollama URL)_:
: <input type="text" name="OLLAMA_URL" value="<?=v($cfg,'OLLAMA_URL')?>"> (e.g. http://127.0.0.1:11434)

_(Ollama model)_:
: <input type="text" name="OLLAMA_MODEL" value="<?=v($cfg,'OLLAMA_MODEL')?>">

> **Optional — Matrix notifications**

_(Matrix homeserver)_:
: <input type="text" name="MATRIX_HOMESERVER" value="<?=v($cfg,'MATRIX_HOMESERVER')?>">

_(Matrix token)_:
: <input type="password" name="MATRIX_TOKEN" value="<?=v($cfg,'MATRIX_TOKEN')?>">

_(Matrix room)_:
: <input type="text" name="MATRIX_ROOM" value="<?=v($cfg,'MATRIX_ROOM')?>">

:shiplog_help_plug:
> ShipLog is **read-only** — it never updates, pulls, or stops anything; it only
> tells you what changes between your running image and the newest one. The
> changelog appears as a small control in the Docker tab's update column.

&nbsp;
: <input type="submit" name="#apply" value="Apply"><input type="button" value="Done" onclick="done()">

</form>

<script>
(function () {
  var port = "<?=v($cfg,'PORT','8484')?>";
  var a = document.getElementById("sl-statuslink");
  if (a) a.innerHTML = 'Status page: <a href="http://' + location.hostname + ':' + port + '/" target="_blank">http://' + location.hostname + ':' + port + '/</a>';
})();
</script>
